    "media:imagetext": "SAFETY\nINFORMATION\n• SINGAPORE AIRLINES\nTAKE OFF \u0026\nLANDING\nBags that cannot fit into overhead compartments or under seats\nwill be stowed in the cargo hold. Please remove spare lithium\nbatteries and valuables from these bags.\nDO NOT REMOVE THIS CARD FROM AIRCRAFT\nIt is a chargeable offence not to obey safety instructions\nfrom our crew, or to remove or tamper with the safety\nequipment on board the aircraft.\nB777-300ER\nEXPLANATION OF SYMBOLS\nEXIT\nLanding on\nground\nLanding\non water\nFasten\nseat belt\nNo\nsmoking\nEmergency\nexit\nDo not take\nbaggage\nRemove high\nheel shoes\nStow large\nPED\nSwitch off\nlightweight PED\nOxygen\nAT ALL TIMES DURING\nTHE FLIGHT\nKeep seatbelts fastened when seated\nFasten\nTighten\nINFANT SEAT BELTS ARE AVAILABLE\nPlease check with cabin crew\nUnfasten\nTake care when opening\noverhead compartments\nNo Smoking\nincluding e-cigarettes\nSMOKING\nIN THE\nTOILET\nSETS OFF\nTHE SMOKE\nALARM\nDURING TURBULENCE\nRemain in your seats with seatbelts fastened, even when in bed mode.\nRemove infants from bassinets and secure with infant seatbelts.\nToilets must not be used\nTaxi-out\nTake-off\nCruise\nLanding\nTaxi-in\nPORTABLE ELECTRONIC DEVICES (PEDs)\nUSAGE\n• The use of large PEDs (such as laptops and notebooks) and DVD\nplayers is not permitted during taxi (for departure \u0026 arrival), take-off\nand landing, and they must be stowed.\n• The use of low power consumption PEDs such as heart pacemaker,\nhearing aids and digital watches is permitted for all phases of flight.\n• Please refer to the information below on the usage\nof lightweight PEDs such as mobile phones and\ntablet. They must not be connected to peripheral\ndevices (such as keyboards, earphones etc.), in-seat\npower supply outlets or the USB/HDMI ports of\nthe Inflight Entertainment System during taxi (for\ndeparture \u0026 arrival), take-off and landing.\n• Voice communications using transmitting PEDs is prohibited at all\n• Charging is only permitted during cruise and for PEDs equipped with\noriginal manufacturer's equipment (OEM) batteries. Use the in-seat\npower supply or USB port to charge PEDs. Do not cover PEDs with\na blanket or pillow or place them inside the seat pocket. Do not\nleave PEDs unattended while charging.\nPhase\nTall\nGSM/Cellular\nWi-Fi\n*\nBluetooth\nOperational reasons and/or\nlocal law may prohibit the\nuse of PEDs. Where such\nconditions exist, all PED\nmust be switched off or put\nin Flight Safe/Airplane mode.\nPlease follow the instructions\nof the crew.\nFlight Safe\n(SM/Cellular\nWi-Fi\nLocal law may prohibit the\nuse of PEDs during taxi-in.\nWhere such conditions exist,\nall PEDs must be switched off.\nPlease follow the instructions\nof the crew.\n*\nBluetooth\nFlight Safe\nA STAR ALLIANCE MEMBER\nSINGAPORE AIRLINES\nA great way to fly",
